{
  "translated_title": "[Fun Learning/Our Children's Study Helper] Fermat",
  "translated_text": "Fermat, a specialized admissions hagwon for special-purpose high schools, is conducting special programs during winter break at Fermat campuses nationwide, including Daechi-dong [a Gangnam neighborhood known as the epicenter of Korea's elite hagwon industry] in Gangnam-gu, Seoul, and Bundang-gu in Seongnam, Gyeonggi Province.

Fermat has prepared two programs for 2008 special-purpose high school admission success, aligned with the Ministry of Education and Human Resources Development's foreign language high school examination policies: prohibition of math and science questions, prohibition of short-answer questions, and questions limited to middle school curriculum content. First, winter break classes will be conducted at each campus. Daechi Campus combines curriculum progression (5 sessions), creative thinking skills (2 sessions), and language thinking skills (2 sessions). Bundang Campus offers curriculum progression (4 sessions), creative thinking skills (2 sessions), and language thinking skills (1 session). Each campus also conducts nationwide mock exams.

Second, weekend intensive lecture programs will be conducted, taught directly by Shin Dong-yeop, CEO of Fermat Edu. Weekend intensives are held only at Daechi and Bundang campuses, combining creative thinking skills (1 session), language thinking skills (1 session), English intensive for foreign language high school preparation (1 session), and nationwide mock exams. Classes begin in January next year, and weekend intensives are also available online. 02-560-8500, 1, www.fermatedu.com"
}

{
  "translated_title": "[Fun Learning/Our Children's Study Helper] Creating Math Prodigies",
  "translated_text": "Yeongjaesagwan Hagwon [Elite Officer Academy Hagwon] (head director Kim Hyeong-jin), which specializes in admissions to Minjok Leadership Academy [a prestigious boarding school] and special purpose high schools, has created a specialized math education program called 'Creating Math Prodigies,' and its franchise hagwons are recruiting students for the winter break.

Recruitment targets students from prospective 3rd grade elementary through 3rd grade middle school, and the curriculum uses 156 levels of specialized textbooks and supplementary materials directly developed by the gifted education division of Saebyeok Haneul Co., Ltd., the educational corporation of Yeongjaesagwan Hagwon. 'Creating Math Prodigies' was developed by Yeongjaesagwan Hagwon, which has the expertise of producing numerous graduates who gained admission to Minjok Leadership Academy and special purpose high schools, in order to cultivate math prodigies who can develop problem-solving abilities through creative thinking.

Through discussion-based presentation learning, it strengthens mathematical and essay-writing abilities, and three hagwon instructors—basic, advanced, and discussion teachers—teach simultaneously in each class. 'Creating Math Prodigies' provides customized education suitable for creative thinking, school records [GPA], math competitions, olympiads, and special purpose high school admissions preparation through a nationwide evaluation system for comprehensive grade analysis and an instructor evaluation certification system. 031-383-3322"
}

