{
  "translated_title": "[Obituary] Lee Ikhoon Language Hagwon Chairman Lee Ikhoon Passes Away",
  "translated_text": "Lee Ikhoon, chairman of Lee Ikhoon Language Hagwon and renowned English hagwon instructor, passed away at 1:30 PM on the 3rd due to chronic illness. He was 61 years old.

Born in Seoul in 1947, Lee studied at Yonsei University and West Coast University in the United States. He began making his name in the hagwon industry as an English hagwon instructor starting in the mid-1990s by publishing English textbooks bearing his name. In 1993, Lee established and operated 'Lee Ikhoon Language Hagwon,' named after himself, and devoted himself to English education while serving as an adjunct professor at Hanyang University and visiting professor at Dankook University.

The deceased underwent prostate cancer surgery in 2005 and continued active teaching and writing while receiving outpatient treatment, but his condition reportedly deteriorated suddenly in recent times. He is survived by his wife Kim Seonsuk and two sons. The funeral parlor is at Samsung Seoul Hospital, and the funeral procession will be held at 8 AM on the 5th. 02-3410-6915"
}

