{
  "translated_title": "[NewsStation/Brief] Government Announces Finalized Measures to Reduce Hagwon Education Costs",
  "translated_text": "<2> Government Announces Finalized Measures to Reduce Hagwon Education Costs\nThe government has finalized and announced measures to reduce hagwon education costs, with the main focus being strengthening public education and improving the admissions system for special purpose high schools.\nThe Ministry of Education, Science and Technology announced on the 3rd that to strengthen public education, they will fully implement a subject classroom system where students move to specialized classrooms for classes, and starting next year, they will fully implement a teacher competency development evaluation system to enhance teachers' professional expertise.\nFor foreign language high school admissions, modified forms of written examinations will be prohibited, and the so-called 'hagwon informant system' that rewards people for reporting improper conduct by hagwons will be introduced starting this December."
