  "translated_text": "Haneul Education Co., Ltd. (www.edusky.co.kr) will hold an 'Admissions Policy Analysis and Business Strategy Briefing' on the 23rd at 11 AM in the auditorium on the 23rd floor of the Hanjin Shipping Building in Yeouido, Yeongdeungpo-gu, Seoul, targeting home-visit learning material teachers, hagwon business operators, and those hoping to start education businesses. At the briefing, Seo Jin-won, CEO of Haneul Education, and Lim Seong-ho, Planning Director of Haneul Education, will introduce future prospects based on changes to high school and university admissions this year and corresponding business strategies for the education industry. They will also forecast trends and future directions for early childhood and elementary/middle/high school education businesses. Participants will receive hagwon and home-visit education admissions counseling manuals and analysis materials for elementary, middle, and high schools nationwide by school. Meanwhile, from the 26th to 29th, briefings on the same topic will be held in four major cities nationwide (Busan, Daegu, Daejeon, Gwangju). The briefing schedules and locations are: △26th at 11 AM at EXCO Convention Center in Buk-gu, Daegu △27th at 11 AM at the Chamber of Commerce in Seo-gu, Gwangju △28th at 11 AM at the Private School Pension Hall in Seo-gu, Daejeon △29th at 11 AM at Kookje Newspaper building in Yeonjeong-gu, Busan. Prior registration through the website is required. 02-761-3200"
