{
  "translated_title": "[News File] Police Arrest Jeffrey Son on Charges of 'SAT Answer Leakage'",
  "translated_text": "Seoul Suseo Police Station announced on the 27th that they have arrested and are investigating hagwon instructor Jeffrey Son (39) on charges of leaking answers to the American college entrance exam (SAT [Scholastic Assessment Test, a standardized test for U.S. college admissions]). According to police, Son is suspected of discovering that questions from the January 27, 2007 test were identical to those from December 2005, and posting those questions and some answers on his internet cafe before the test began in the United States.\n▶See page A14 of this paper's February 10th edition\nStar instructor summoned also shows signs of SAT question leakage\nA post believed to have been written by Son contained the message \"The December 2005 test questions were used identically in January 2007. Students like me who solved the December test would have received perfect scores,\" along with organized answers. When suspicions of question leakage arose from this test, the Educational Testing Service (ETS) [the U.S. organization that administers the SAT] invalidated the scores of all Korean test-takers."
}

