{
  "translated_title": "[Busan/Gyeongnam] 14 Teachers from Baejeong School Foundation Dismissed Over Hiring Corruption",
  "translated_text": "Teachers from Busan's Baejeong School Foundation who were hired through corrupt methods have been dismissed. The Busan Metropolitan Office of Education announced on the 12th that the Baejeong School Foundation recently held a board meeting and decided to cancel the appointments and acceptances of 14 teachers involved in hiring corruption.\n\nThese teachers were hired by paying the board chairman 50 million to 100 million won [approximately $38,000–75,000 USD] to receive exam questions in advance, and received fines. However, they either avoided sanctions due to the expiration of disciplinary statute of limitations, or received light disciplinary actions such as salary cuts and suspensions from the school's own disciplinary committee. Accordingly, the Busan Metropolitan Office of Education has been putting strong pressure on the school foundation since August last year by halting personnel cost support for these teachers and pushing to reduce the number of classes at high schools under the Baejeong School Foundation."
}

{
  "translated_title": "[Daegu/Gyeongsangbuk-do] Half-price Foreign Language Education for SME Employees",
  "translated_text": "The Daegu-Gyeongsangbuk-do Regional Small and Medium Business Administration has opened special foreign language course classes to help local small and medium enterprises (SMEs) enter overseas markets. Any employee of regional SMEs can apply. They will receive support for 50% of tuition fees (40,000-60,000 won [approximately $30-45 USD]) and textbooks. The application period runs until the 24th of next month. Each class is limited to 10 students on a first-come, first-served basis. Classes will be divided into three sections - English, Japanese, and Chinese conversation - and will be held at Seoseo Herald Language Hagwon (Sindang-dong, Dalseo-gu) for two months starting in March. Class times can be selected from morning or afternoon sessions. Student recruitment will also take place in March, July, and September. To apply, download the application form from the website and send it by fax (053-626-8771). 053-659-2244"
}

