  "translated_title": "[Fun Study] Haneul Education Central Hagwon University Admission Strategy Information Session",
  "translated_text": "Haneul Education Central Hagwon will hold university admissions information sessions from Saturday, June 8th at 11 AM, starting at Seoul Jinseon Girls' High School auditorium and continuing until the 11th in Seoul, Gyeonggi Province, and major metropolitan cities, with the theme 'Emergency Analysis of June Mock Exam, CSAT [College Scholastic Ability Test, Korea's national university entrance exam] A·B Type Grade-Level Change Predictions, and Rolling Admissions Strategy'.

The information sessions will be held in Seoul (8th), Gyeonggi (9th), Incheon (9th), Daegu (10th), Busan (10th), Daejeon (11th), and Gwangju (11th). These sessions will cover: △2014 CSAT question trends and subject-specific preparation strategies based on the June 5th mock exam results △CSAT A·B type difficulty forecasts and test-taking strategies △predicted changes in each grade bracket according to English and Korean A-type selection ratios.

The instructors will be Lim Seong-ho, CEO of Haneul Education, and Jang Moon-seong, Evaluation Director of Haneul Education Central Hagwon. Advance reservation is required through the website (www.kteacher.co.kr). Admissions materials will be provided only to those with reservations. For detailed session schedules, refer to the website. 02-2070-0101"
